Functional variants

load("data/export_functional_variants/phenoscanner-entries.RDS")

#Find TYK2 missense variants
TYK2_missense <- functional_variants$TYK2$results %>% 
  filter(consequence == "missense") %>%  
  distinct(rsid) %>% pull()

TYK2_missense #rs55886939, rs34536443, rs35018800, rs55882956, rs12720356, 
 [1] "rs55886939"  "rs34536443"  "rs35018800"  "rs55882956"  "rs12720356" 
 [6] "rs139954108" "rs2304256"   "rs188833543" "rs55762744"  "rs144960992"
              #rs139954108, rs2304256,rs188833543, rs55762744, rs144960992

#give betas and se for eQTL and T1D risk (note, this is not MR!)
TYK2_eqtl %>%
  filter(SNP %in% TYK2_missense) %>%
    mutate(Fstat = (beta.exposure/se.exposure)^2) %>% 
  select(SNP, beta.outcome, se.outcome, pval.outcome, beta.exposure, pval.exposure, Fstat) %>%
  mutate(across(!matches(c("SNP", "pval.outcome", "pval.exposure")), function(x) signif(x, digits = 2)))

#Select only rs12720356 and rs2304256 (as p for their exposure is < 10^-5) and run MR
TYK2_eqtl_funcvar_mr <- TYK2_eqtl %>%
  filter(SNP %in% c("rs12720356", "rs2304256")) %>%
  TwoSampleMR::mr_singlesnp() %>%
  mutate(exp_b = exp(b), 
         lo_95 = exp(b - (1.96 * se)),
         hi_95 = exp(b + (1.96 * se))) %>%
    mutate(across(starts_with(c("b", "se","p", "exp_b", "lo", "hi")), function(x) signif(x, digits = 2)))

  TYK2_eqtl_funcvar_mr %>% 
    select(-id.exposure, -id.outcome, -samplesize) %>% 
    knitr::kable()
